 Our team develops the NVIDIA DriveWorks SDK with the goal to provide a scalable software stack and framework to build autonomous vehicles software stacks. We are seeking build engineers with interests in build infrastructure and systems and how to improve engineering productivity to work as part of NVIDIA‚Äôs autonomous vehicles team.
 What you will be doing:
 Maintain and enhance our build system
 Developing tools and new frameworks to make the job of software building and deployment easier.
 Reviewing code for the software build architecture
 Creating plugins that will improve the automation and packaging process
 Integrating our system with company-wide build and test harnesses
 Actively participate on the releases of the software
 What we need to see:
 BS or higher in computer science or a related engineering discipline or equivalent experience
 10+ years of experience
 Experienced Linux user
 Background with version control systems GIT
 Strong knowledge of build systems such as Make, CMake and/or Bazel
 Deep understanding of CI/CD processes
 Strong knowledge of scripting and Python
 Excellent C and C++ programming skills
 Experience on integrating 3rd party libraries into existing codebases.
 Self-motivation and a great teammate
 Ways to stand out from the crowd:
 Strong knowledge of Bazel build system
 Be hands-on and work well within a team of algorithm, software and hardware engineers, with a significant level of detail orientation and a penchant for data organization and presentation
